headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton finished with 24 points and 11 assists, and Obi Toppin made six 3-pointers and added 20 points to help the Indiana Pacers beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 119-103 on Monday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton and Obi Toppin lead 3-point flurry to help Pacers beat Timberwolves 119-103

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner had 32 points and eight assists, Paolo Banchero added 30 points and seven rebounds and the Orlando Magic sent the Los Angeles Lakers to their third straight loss, 118-106 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner and Banchero power the Magic to a 118-106 win over the struggling Lakers

headlines.description: — Jakob Poeltl had 21 points and 11 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors beat the Washington Wizards 112-104 on Monday night to stop a four-game slide.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poeltl and Quickley help the Raptors beat the Wizards 112-104

headlines.description: — Naji Marshall scored 22 points off the bench to lead the Dallas Mavericks to a 120-101 rout of the Brooklyn Nets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Naji Marshall's 22 leads Mavericks to 120-101 rout of Nets in Anthony Davis' return

headlines.description: — Karlo Matkovic had a season-high 19 points and eight assists, Antonio Reeves had five 3-pointers and 17 points and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Philadelphia 76ers 112-99 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans use balanced scoring to send the 76ers to their 5th straight loss, 112-99

headlines.description: — Coby White scored 37 points to lead the streaking Chicago Bulls over the short-handed Denver Nuggets 129-119 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores 37, Bulls beat Nuggets 129-119

headlines.description: — Devin Booker made a mid-range jumper with 2.4 seconds remaining to lift the Phoenix Suns over the Milwaukee Bucks 108-106 on Monday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker hits clutch jumper with 2.4 seconds left to lift Suns over Bucks 108-106 for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 25 points, seven rebounds and eight assists before suffering a hard foul and leaving in the Boston Celtics' 113-95 win over the Sacramento Kings on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum injured in Celtics' 113-95 win over Kings
